TITLE: 2 weeks after police found 4 slain students, here's where the investigation stands
SUMMARY: Two weeks after the stabbing deaths of four University of Idaho students, dozens of local, state and federal investigators are still working to determine who carried out the brutal attack.

TITLE: Police claim a 16-year-old confessed on Instagram video chat to killing a girl and asked for help disposing of body
SUMMARY: A teenager has been charged as an adult after police claim he killed another young person and confessed on an Instagram video chat, asking for help disposing of the body.

TITLE: 2 injured in a drive-by shooting after a funeral service at a Nashville church
SUMMARY: Nashville authorities are investigating a drive-by shooting after a funeral service at a church Saturday that left two people wounded, police said.

TITLE: Sen. Chris Murphy doesn't think Democrats have 60 votes for assault weapons ban
SUMMARY: Democratic Sen. Chris Murphy of Connecticut said Senate Democrats don't have the 60 votes needed to advance an assault weapons ban bill but expressed optimism on CNN's "State of the Union" that something could get done in the next Congress if Democrats keep their seat in Georgia.

TITLE: Schiff says January 6 committee will decide what goes in the final report 'in a collaborative manner'
SUMMARY: House Intelligence Committee Chairman Adam Schiff, who also sits on the House committee investigating the Jan. 6, 2021, insurrection, said Sunday that he doesn't believe the committee's upcoming report would focus almost entirely on Donald Trump.

TITLE: Arkansas GOP governor says Trump's meeting with Holocaust denier is 'very troubling' and 'empowering' for extremism
SUMMARY: Former President Donald Trump's meeting last week with White nationalist and Holocaust denier Nick Fuentes was "very troubling" and "empowering" for extremism, Republican Gov. Asa Hutchinson said Sunday.

TITLE: Early voting begins in some Georgia counties as Warnock and Walker sprint to December 6 runoff
SUMMARY: A week-long early voting period begins Saturday in some Georgia counties as Democratic Sen. Raphael Warnock and Republican challenger Herschel Walker enter a week-and-a-half, post-Thanksgiving sprint to their December 6 runoff election.

TITLE: How JCPenney plans to win back shoppers
SUMMARY: Marc Rosen didn't flinch when he was offered the top job at JCPenney last year.

TITLE: A rail strike won't screw up your holidays. Here's how it'll affect you in other ways
SUMMARY: So once again the nation and its economy is facing the risk of a massive freight railroad strike, this one as soon as Dec. 9. But about the only thing you don't need to worry about it is whether it will affect your holiday shopping plans. (It won't.)

TITLE: Frontier Airlines no longer has a customer service phone line
SUMMARY: Customers who need flight information or want to make changes to travel plans can no longer call Frontier Airlines and speak to an agent, the company confirmed to CNN Saturday.
